Author: Daniel Lin 

Below are some helpful documents that I have read that provides useful information on Ethercat. This document will be updated frequently. 

Ethercat Specifications Part 1
https://docs.google.com/a/onid.oregonstate.edu/viewer?a=v&pid=sites&srcid=dW1pY2guZWR1fGF0cmlhc3xneDo0MmZiNGZiMDAyYzJlMzhh

Ethercat Slave Implementation Guide (Does not contain specific informations about implementing the slave. Rather, it contains useful terms and concepts helpful for slave implementation)
http://www.ethercat.org/pdf/english/ETG2200_V2i0i0_SlaveImplementationGuide.pdf

Ethercat Knolwedge Base from Beckhoff. 
http://www.ethercat.org/login.aspx?ReturnUrl=%2fmemberarea%2fen%2fknowledge_base.htm

Documentation about CAN and CANOpen protocols that are essential to Ethercat
http://www.copleycontrols.com/Motion/pdf/CANopenProgrammersManual.pdf#page=32&zoom=auto,63,476

Stackoverflow page that contains vital documentations about Ethercat
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17146332/how-can-i-study-ethercat-without-any-background

Ethercat Master Documentation
http://etherlab.org/download/ethercat/ethercat-1.5.2.pdf
